Movie S2. Interaction Network Connecting His33 and Asp35 of the J-Domain with the Catalytic Residues Glu171 and Lys70 of DnaK, Related to Figure 6 . Many residues of the network have been shown to be important for DnaJ function (Val389, Leu390, Leu391, Leu392; Kumar et al., 2011; Laufen et al., 1999; Mayer et al., 1999; Vogel et al., 2006b); Glu171 (Vogel et al., 2006a), or for allostery in Hsp70s (Asp481, Kityk et al., 2012; Leu484, Asp148, Kityk et al., 2015), or both (Arg167, Asn170, Thr173, Suh et al., 1998; Vogel et al., 2006b; D393, Vogel et al., 2006b; Arg151, Pro143, Vogel et al., 2006a).
